vol_text: Okay. When-when somebody has asthma, their lungs are like hypersensitive. She asked me to, like, to promise her of no alcohol, no drugs. Then I'll pick you up by 12:00. vol_text: Alcohol can have some dangerous effects on your body. So along with contributing to high blood pressure, it can have a big impact on your liver, which you need to keep in mind. So your liver has several different roles in your body. First, it helps process excess fatty acids before they get distributed to the rest of your body. It also helps process alcohol and other drugs. So when you have an excess of alcohol, your liver can't work as efficiently and the fatty acids build up, and over time, your liver won't be able to work as well.
